  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior/Design Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>1. Design &amp; Drafting</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop and prepare detailed shop drawings, erection drawings, and reinforcement detailing for precast concrete components (e.g., beams, columns, wall panels, slabs, staircases).</li>\n  <li>Modify and optimize designs based on project requirements, production capabilities, and site constraints.</li>\n  <li>Ensure drawings comply with relevant codes, standards, and client specifications</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2. Coordination &amp; Communication</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Liaise with architects, consultants, and main contractors to resolve design discrepancies.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with the production department to ensure designs are practical for manufacturing and installation.</li>\n  <li>Attend design coordination meetings with stakeholders to address technical queries.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3. Technical Calculations &amp; Analysis</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform structural calculations for load-bearing capacity, reinforcement requirements, and stability of precast elements.</li>\n  <li>Evaluate alternative design solutions for cost savings and efficiency improvements.</li>\n  <li>Use structural analysis software to verify designs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>4. Quality &amp; Compliance</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ensure all designs comply with safety regulations, industry standards, and company quality procedures.</li>\n  <li>Review and approve final drawings before production release.</li>\n  <li>Conduct site visits when necessary to verify installation and alignment with design intent.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Qualifications &amp; Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s Degree in Civil Engineering, Structural Engineering, or related field.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of experience in precast design or structural engineering.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Etabs, Prokon and structural analysis software.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of relevant design codes.</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical skills and attention to detail.</li>\n  <li>Good communication and coordination skills with multidisciplinary teams.</li>\n</ul>",
